<h1>Boise, Idaho</h1>
<p style="margin-bottom: 15px; margin-top: 5px;"><strong>Population:</strong> 211,473</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 15px;"><strong>Metro Area Population:</strong> 559,059</p>
<p><em>In May of 2009 Boise was rated the 4th best city to live, work, and play by Kiplinger.<br />In April of 2007 Boise was rated the 3rd best place for business and careers.</em></p>
</div>
<div style="clear: both; padding-top: 20px;">
<h3>Trends of Employment</h3>
<p>Technology investment and high-tech industry have become increasingly important in Boise. The call center industry is also a major source of employment. Agriculture, forest products, and mining are traditional industries; while tourism, retail trade, healthcare, and business adn information services are growth sectors.</p>
<h3>Cost of Living</h3>
<p>Boise City-Nampa Metro Area's income per capita is $22,613, which includes all adults and children. The median household income is $47,399.</p>
<h3>Transportation</h3>
<p>The average commute time is 20 minutes. ValleyRide bus system offers fixed-line bus service in the area. Twelve national and regional airlines serve the Boise Air Terminal (BOI).</p>
